sil record and typical characteristics of each genus. The state of chameleons in the modern world is also depicted, complete with new information on the most serious threats to these remarkable reptiles.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aChameleons. 7aSCIENCE / Life Sciences / Biology.2bisacsh1 aAnderson, Christopher V., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBolet, Arnau, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aEvans, Susan E., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHerrel, Anthony, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHerrel, Anthony, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aHigham, Timothy E., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJenkins, Richard, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMeasey, John G., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMenegon, Michele, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRaselimanana, Achille, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aStuart-Fox, Devi, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aTilbury, Colin R., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aTolley, Krystal A., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aTolley, Krystal A., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013z978311069042240uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052095738140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520957381423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520957381/original  a978-3-11-069042-2  University of California Press Back